{"version":3,"kind":"Notebook","sha256":"c34718673df3ae12831407018cddb33e5c869acea4def2b6e0897c8ada392796","slug":"land-cover-thematic-accuracy","location":"/content/land_cover_thematic_accuracy.ipynb","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Land Cover Thematic Accuracy","content_includes_title":false,"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3 (ipykernel)","language":"python"},"numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"exports":[{"format":"ipynb","filename":"land_cover_thematic_accuracy.ipynb","url":"/oqapi-jupyter-book/build/land_cover_thematic_-42ee4bce3ba20c924f78ec32ed08b251.ipynb"}]},"widgets":{},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This indicator evaluates the agreement between OSM land cover data and the CORINE Land Cover (CLC) dataset.\nIt can be applied either across multiple CLC classes or for selected classes individually.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"j5JE2zK7Dh"}],"key":"B2hdUUIKsY"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"OSM features are assigned to CLC Level 2 classes based\non their landuse=* and natural=* tags.\nThe spatial intersection of OSM polygons with CLC\npolygons produces composite geometries carrying both the OSM- and CLC-derived class labels. This step ensures\nthat discrepancies in class definitions can be directly\nanalyzed at the polygon level. Areas where one of the\ndatasets is not available are ignored.\nFor the defined area of interest, polygons resulting from\nthe intersection of OSM and CLC data are aggregated\ninto a confusion matrix. From this, we calculate class-\nspecific and overall accuracy metrics, including precision,\nrecall, and the F1 score. All metrics are area-weighted,\nensuring that the spatial extent of polygons is taken into\naccount rather than treating features as equally weighted\nunits. This approach enables a systematic evaluation of the\nthematic consistency of OSM land cover data with respect\nto authoritative CLC reference data.\nThe result value is calculated as the area-weighted F1-\nscore normalised to a range of 0 to 1. Values below 0.6\nare considered low thematic agreement, values between\n0.6 and 0.85 as medium agreement and values above 0.85\nas high agreement between OSM and CLC.","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"xqj1hAnxPU"}],"key":"skegPpA5UZ"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Methods and Data","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"rkkPbbOLMC"}],"identifier":"methods-and-data","label":"Methods and Data","html_id":"methods-and-data","implicit":true,"key":"CKkOVoUvN2"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"-> Extrinsic approach.","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"NuFFNCznS1"}],"key":"WmtFzUtBfi"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The OSM features are assigned to CLC Level 2 classes based on their landuse=* and natural=* tags, as shown in the table below. The spatial intersection of OSM polygons with CLC polygons produces composite geometries carrying both the OSM- and CLC-derived class labels. This step ensures that discrepancies in class definitions can be directly analyzed at the polygon level. Areas where one of the\ndatasets is not available are ignored. For the defined area of interest, polygons resulting from the intersection of OSM and CLC data are aggregated into a confusion matrix. From this, we calculate class- specific and overall accuracy metrics, including precision, recall, and the F1 score. All metrics are area-weighted, ensuring that the spatial extent of polygons is taken into account rather than treating features as equally weighted units. This approach enables a systematic evaluation of the thematic consistency of OSM land cover data with respect to authoritative CLC reference data. The result value is calculated as the area-weighted F1- score normalised to a range of 0 to 1.","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"key":"dtlYZPe4dK"}],"key":"JE0yKG3Xtz"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Low thematic accuracy (< 0.6)","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"nRbGRb1Zjg"}],"key":"t0lRut2Cow"}],"key":"kw4s9lO8HK"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Medium thematic accuracy (0.6 - 0.85)","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"key":"mpP6iUs0KZ"}],"key":"Jbj88C4J5R"}],"key":"HTsTopD44K"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"High thematic accuracy (> 0.85)","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"key":"gvaULLY9l9"}],"key":"L8kNe1ZqGs"}],"key":"EGHi6F54vu"}],"key":"oXadqIh0WD"},{"type":"image","url":"/myst_assets_folderimages/land_cover_thematic_acc_pastures_detmold.png","alt":"land_cover_thematic_comp","position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"key":"KDFFz1iNQp"},{"